Inheritance : 
*************
inheritanc in java is a mecanism in which one object aquire all the property 
of its parent object

A --- > B : single 

A-->B-->C : multilevel

A-->B   : hierirchical
|-->C

A-->C  : multiple - this is not supported in java
B--|


***************************
Access modifier : 
public : anywhere
private : within class only
protected : within package , out side the package using inheritance
default : within package only

***************************
Encaptulation : 
Encapsulation in Java is the process by which data (variables) 
and the code that acts upon them (methods) are integrated as a 
single unit. By encapsulating a class's variables, other classes
cannot access them, and only the methods of the class can access 
 them

************************************************************
abstraction :
**************
Abstraction in Java is a process of hiding the implementation details
from the user and showing only the functionality to the user.

How can we acheive abstraction in java : 
two ways to achieve abstraction in java : 

Abstract class : partial abstraction
abstract method and instance method

Interface : 100% abstraction
abstract method


***********************************
Abstract method :  method without body

public void display();

Instance method : 

public void display()
{
}

